headline: Delta, United Airlines, Latham, eXp World, and RE/MAX Stocks Trade Up, What You Need To Know

headline: Airfares Continue to Rise as Carriers Push Premium Seats
summary: Travel demand was dented earlier this year as rising geopolitical tensions and uncertainty around President Trump's sweeping tariffs made consumers anxious about the economy.  United Airlines and American Airlines notched smaller gains on their top lines for the third quarter, saying that revenue from pricier premium-cabin seats outpaced sales in the main cabin.

headline: Wall Street Analysts Think Delta (DAL) Could Surge 25.22%: Read This Before Placing a Bet
summary: The mean of analysts' price targets for Delta (DAL) points to a 25.2% upside in the stock. While this highly sought-after metric has not proven reasonably effective, strong agreement among analysts in raising earnings estimates does indicate an upside in the stock.

headline: With More Adults Admitting To Celebrating Halloween in 2025, THC Pioneer Delta Beverages Launches New Campaign To Own Spooky Season
summary: Delta Beverages, the number one THC drink brand in the U.S. by volume, is taking over this year as the unofficial beverage of adult Halloween. Delta has unveiled its newest campaign following its recent rebrand that brings "There's A Delta for That™" to life for all of Halloween's micro moments.
